# ============================================================================
# Repo-root ignores ONLY.
#
# This is a two-app monorepo. Each app keeps its own build-output rules in its
# own folder so either is self-contained and portable:
#   - android/.gitignore   (Gradle / Kotlin / Android Studio)
#   - windows/.gitignore   (.NET / Visual Studio / Rider / dotnet)
#
# Keep this file limited to things that legitimately appear at the repo root
# (OS/editor noise, an IDE opened on the whole repo, shared reference material).
# ============================================================================

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~

# IDE / build caches that show up at the repo root when a tool is opened or run
# from here (the real builds live under android/ and windows/). Anchored with a
# leading slash so they only match at the root — the per-app folders ignore
# their own copies.
/.idea/
*.iml
/.gradle/
/.kotlin/

# Reverse-engineered reference material — third-party, shared across both apps,
# never push.
/decompiled/

# Signing material — NEVER commit. The actual keys live OUTSIDE this repo and
# are injected in CI from encrypted GitHub Actions secrets. These unanchored
# patterns match in any subfolder (e.g. android/keystore.properties) as a
# safety net. See docs/SIGNING.md.
keystore.properties
*.keystore
*.jks
*.pfx
*.p12
*.snk
